item.title: Making a no-ip help plz
item.dc:creator: @Vince Vince`
item.description:
@Vince wrote:

On the left hand side click Special Application Ports. This will bring you to the following menu.
We will list a series of lines here that will show you exactly how to configure the router. MoparScape requires you to forward the 43594 ports. Go ahead and enter the settings shown above into the Special Application page.
You should see another page of settings that need to be entered into one of the blank lines on your router’s Special Application page. Go ahead and enter those settings now. Check the “Enable”.

When you are finished, click the Enter button at the bottom of the page to save your settings.

Then You’re Finished.

[glow=red,2,300]Vince`[/glow]

item.title: Making a no-ip help plz
item.dc:creator: @Vince Vince`
item.description:
@Vince wrote:

Right Click on “My Network Places” (On Your Desktop) -> Double click “Local Area Connection” -> Go to Support Tab, You should see “Default Gateway”, next to it there are 4 Sets of Numbers, Mine are 192.168.1.1, Type that in your Addressbar, then a password authentication should appear, then You’re on your own. That’s all I can do.

Go to -> www.portforward.com For More Help!

[glow=red,2,300]Vince`[/glow]
